attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, for GNU/Linux 2.6.9, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a backdoor that masquerades its process name as `[syslogd]`. It opens a raw socket to listen for incoming commands, which are decrypted using a simple XOR cipher. The backdoor supports remote command execution via `popen`, writing received data to a file named `system.conf`, and updating its encryption key. The results of the executed commands are XOR-encrypted and exfiltrated back to the attacker in a custom-crafted network packet.
